Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters who replace the phone number of the bank has increased.
This is reported by Kommersant with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator provided telecom operators with information on more than 2,500 numbers from which customers of various financial organizations called.
In 189 cases, operators found a replacement number.
Another 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases a restriction on the use of financial services was set.
Deputy Head of the Information Security Department of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced the change of number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to the warnings of the Central Bank about fraudulent calls, referring to the lack of such an obligation in the law "On Communications".
In the Bank "Opening", Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the change of number.
As reported in the press service of “Beeline”, part of the information about fraudulent calls, which was transmitted to the Central Bank, was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are really used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would lead to disruptions in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of numbers of fraudsters, to which the operator will address every call to check the number.
He explained that in order to establish such a base, the legislation would need to be amended.
