On September 27, Chairman of the Federation Council Committee on Economic Policy Andrey Kutepov sent a letter to the Minister of Economic Development Maxim Oreshkin and the Minister of Finance Anton Siluanov with a proposal to express a position on initiatives of the constituent entities of the Federation to improve legislation in the field of support for small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs).
It is time to establish interregional relations
The Federation Council Committee on Economic Policy summarized the information received from the regions on their business development and legalization programs, as well as the results of such programs.
In their letters, the regions told the senators about the problems of SME development and sent proposals to improve the current legislation.
“To date, communication between the regions is insufficiently established, as a result of which the business community in all regions of the visit by senators was marked by the question of the lack of information on regional programs for the development of entrepreneurship in the whole country,” said Andrey Kutepov.
In the annex to the letter, which was sent to the Government, he presented a set of positive developments of the regions on the legalization of self-employment and consolidated data from the regions with proposals and issues (available to the editorial office).
