The exchange of information on positive developments in the regions could give impetus to the development of entrepreneurship as a whole.
The first step to such an exchange will be to send the information available to the Committee on Economic Policy,” the senator told the “Parliamentary newspaper”.
Useful experience
Today, in many regions of the country, support programs for small and medium-sized businesses have been adopted and are successfully operating.
For example, in the Vologda region, there is an Entrepreneurship Support Center, which, in addition to financial support measures, assists businessmen in conducting certification of finished products.
In the Ivanovo region, a business support system has been developed, providing for the implementation of the principle of one window through multifunctional centers.
In the Krasnodar Territory, start-up agricultural consumer cooperatives are provided with grants at the expense of the regional budget.
In the Oryol region there is a cluster development center.
The Amur region, within the framework of the federal project "Acceleration of small and medium-sized enterprises", provides for the possibility of subsidizing business incubators created on the basis of existing non-state coworking centers at the expense of the federal budget.
And in a number of other regions, special support measures are being taken for youth entrepreneurship.
The self-employed continue to pull out of the shadows
According to the regional authorities, a number of changes in the current legislation should be made to better support small and medium-sized businesses.
For example, the Arkhangelsk region proposed to replace the term "self-employment" with "entrepreneurship", since this "is most consistent with the content of the state service to promote the self-employment of unemployed citizens."
In the Ivanovo region, it is considered necessary to amend the list of activities performed by self-employed citizens, including activities for finishing and repairing residential premises, country houses, and conducting physical training classes.
The Bryansk region considers it important to strengthen control over unscrupulous dairy producers with the help of the veterinary system "Mercury".
And in Kostroma and Magadan regions advocate for the consolidation of the concept of "social entrepreneurship" and directions of support for social entrepreneurship in the regulatory and legal field.
All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized enterprises, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills.
"All proposals from the regions will be taken into account in the preparation of state programs to support small and medium-sized enterprises, and the most important will be developed in the form of specific bills," Andrey Kutepov assured.
