Pavel Ustinov joined the pickets in support of the defendants of the "Moscow case"
Actor Pavel Ustinov joined a series of single pickets "Freedom to all", which are held on Friday at the presidential administration building in the Old Square in Moscow, reports the correspondent of "Interfax".
The series of pickets began on September 18 in support of Ustinov himself and has continued every day since.
Currently, the participants of the action, replacing each other, stand holding a poster with the inscription "Freedom to all" and the names of those convicted and arrested after uncoordinated rallies in Moscow in the summer of 2019.
In addition to Ustinov, on the poster the names of Yegor Zhukov, Kirill Zhukov, Daniil Beglets, Yevgeny Kovalenko, Konstantin Kotov, Ivan Podkopaev, Aidar Gubaidulin, Alexey Minyaylo, Sergei Fomin, Samariddin Rajabov, Nikita Cirtsov, Eduard Malyshevsky, Vladislavitsy.
On September 16, the Tver court of Moscow sentenced 24-year-old Ustinov to 3.5 years in a general regime colony on charges of using violence against a Rosgvardiya OMON fighter at an uncoordinated action on August 3 in the center of Moscow (part 2 of Article 318 of the Criminal Code).
After that, on September 20, at the request of the Prosecutor General's Office, the court changed Ustinov's measure of restraint from detention to a non-refoulement subscription.
Thus, the petition for the release of Ustinov received more than 112 thousand signatures in a day.
Artists of the theater and cinema began a flash mob in support of a colleague.
